1 WHEREAS, it is imperative that collegiate women's opportunities to compete athletically are
2 protected on the basis of sex; and
3 WHEREAS, NCAA member institutions have an obligation under Title-IX to ensure equality
4 of benefits and opportunities in athletic programs on the basis of sex;
5 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF NORTH DAKOTA, THE
6 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING THEREIN:
7 That the Sixty-ninth Legislative Assembly calls on the NCAA to revoke its transgender
8 student-athlete eligibility policy, which directly discriminates against female student athletes in
9 collegiate women's sports; and
10 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that the NCAA protect the integrity of collegiate women's
11 sports by forbidding transgender identifying males from competing on any women's sports
12 roster or in any collegiate competition; and
13 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that the NCAA require its member conferences to conform
14 to a biological sex-based policy across all sports and all divisions; and
15 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that all sports-governing bodies in the United States protect
16 the category of women's sports for biological women and girls; and
17 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that the Secretary of State send copies of this resolution to
18 the President of the NCAA, the President of the National Junior College Athletic Association, the
19 President of the NAIA, and the President of the United States College Athletic Association.
